### 0. Health Check
GET http://localhost:8081/api/v1/emails/health

### 1. Enviar e-mail de teste simples (Sem HTML e sem anexos)
POST http://localhost:8081/api/v1/emails
Content-Type: multipart/form-data; boundary=WebAppBoundary

--WebAppBoundary
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="to"

jaymesanches@gmail.com
--WebAppBoundary
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="subject"

Teste de Envio Simples
--WebAppBoundary
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="body"

Olá! Este é um e-mail simples (texto plano) enviado via multipart/form-data.
--WebAppBoundary--


### 2. Enviar e-mail formatado em HTML
POST http://localhost:8081/api/v1/emails
Content-Type: multipart/form-data; boundary=WebAppBoundary

--WebAppBoundary
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="to"

jaymesanches@gmail.com
--WebAppBoundary
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="subject"

Teste de E-mail HTML
--WebAppBoundary
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="isHtml"

true
--WebAppBoundary
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="body"

<div style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif;">
  <h1>Olá, Jayme!</h1>
  <p>Este é um teste de mensagem contendo tags <strong>HTML</strong>.</p>
  <p style="color: blue;">Texto azul para testar a formatação!</p>
</div>
--WebAppBoundary--


### 3. Enviar e-mail com HTML e múltiplos anexos inline
POST http://localhost:8081/api/v1/emails
Content-Type: multipart/form-data; boundary=WebAppBoundary

--WebAppBoundary
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="to"

jaymesanches@gmail.com
--WebAppBoundary
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="subject"

Teste com Múltiplos Anexos
--WebAppBoundary
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="isHtml"

true
--WebAppBoundary
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="body"

<h3>E-mail com Anexos</h3>
<p>Por favor, verifique os relatórios de teste em anexo.</p>
--WebAppBoundary
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="attachments"; filename="documento_teste.txt"
Content-Type: text/plain

Conteúdo do documento de texto anexado pelo arquivo api.http. Funciona super bem!
--WebAppBoundary
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="attachments"; filename="dados.csv"
Content-Type: text/csv

id,nome,cargo
1,Jayme,Dev
2,Fulano,QA
--WebAppBoundary--
